main event: Eight to ten round, luminous objects were observed suspended in the sky at Reese A.F.B. on June 11, 1954.
interesting points: The objects were described as garish whitish color and rather faint in intensity,The objects seemed to pulsate or vibrate at intervals,The sighting lasted for 15 minutes,The objects were located at an altitude of 30,000 to 40,000 feet,The report concluded there was insufficient data for analysis.
